  <section class="section" id="faq">
    <div class="section-label">FAQ</div>
    <h2>Common questions</h2>
    <div class="faq">

      <details>
        <summary>Is this an official Microsoft or Bing extension?</summary>
        <div class="faq-body">
          <p><strong>No.</strong></p>
          <p>Points Harvest is an independent tool with no affiliation with Microsoft, Bing, or the Rewards program. It is not endorsed, authorized, or supported by Microsoft in any way.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>Will my Bing account get banned?</summary>
        <div class="faq-body">
          There is a risk — <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/servicesagreement/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Microsoft's Rewards Terms of Service</a> prohibit automated point collection. Points Harvest is transparent about this: the extension shows a warning on first launch. It uses human-like randomized timing and does not spoof anything, but no tool can guarantee your account is safe. Use it at your own discretion.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>Is it really free and open-source? Any catch?</summary>
        <div class="faq-body">
          Yes, completely free and <a href="{{ site.githubUrl }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">open-source</a>. No account, no login, no subscription. The source code is publicly available on GitHub — you can inspect exactly what the extension does. It runs entirely on your device with no tracking or analytics of any kind.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>How many points can I earn per day?</summary>
        <div class="faq-body">
          Points Harvest automates four phases each run: Explore on Bing activity cards, Daily Set tiles, More Activities tiles, and PC search farming up to your daily cap. Users in the United States can potentially earn around 7,900 points per month through the extension alone. For a full breakdown of every earning category and what the extension automates, see <a href="/blog/maximum-rewards-points/">How Many Microsoft Rewards Points Can You Actually Earn?</a>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>Does it need my Microsoft password?</summary>
        <div class="faq-body">
          No. Points Harvest never asks for or stores your credentials. It operates entirely through your already-signed-in Chrome session on <code>rewards.bing.com</code> and <code>bing.com</code> — the same way you'd use those sites normally.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>Does it work in Edge or Firefox?</summary>
        <div class="faq-body">
          Other <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chromium_(web_browser)#Browsers_based_on_Chromium" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Chromium-based browsers</a> like Brave, Opera, and Vivaldi support unpacked extensions the same way Chrome does. Edge is more complex — it is primarily designed to install extensions from the Chrome Web Store rather than loading them unpacked. Firefox is not supported; it uses a different extension format.
        </div>
      </details>

    </div>
  </section>
